-- Polish Shares: PKO Bank Polski, Warsaw Stock Exchange Move
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-05-14T15:45:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-14/polish-shares-pko-bank-polski-warsaw-stock-exchange-move.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  lost 1.9 percent
to 2,137.12 at the end of trading in Warsaw, the lowest level
since Jan. 11.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange (GPW)  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  PKO Bank Polski SA (PKO)  , the country’s largest lender,
slumped 2.5 percent to 31.5 zloty, a three-week low after saying
its bad-loan provisions jumped 20 percent in the first quarter.  Warsaw Stock Exchange (GPW PW), the operator of the Polish
bourse, slid 3.8 percent to 35.47 zloty, the weakest level since
Jan. 12 after proposing a lower-than-expected dividend.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw 
